## Employee Attrition Prediction using Machine Learning

A complete end-to-end data science project predicting whether an employee is likely 
to leave a company, built on the IBM HR Analytics dataset (1,470 records).

### What's covered
- Exploratory Data Analysis (EDA) — attrition by department, role, income, tenure, and work-life balance
- Data preprocessing — one-hot encoding, feature scaling, class imbalance handling
- Model training & comparison — Logistic Regression, Random Forest, Gradient Boosting
- Evaluation — Precision, Recall, F1-Score, ROC-AUC, Confusion Matrix
- Feature importance — top 10 drivers of employee exit
- HR recommendations — written for a non-technical business audience

### Key finding
Overtime is the single strongest predictor of attrition — stronger than salary alone.
Sales Representatives show a ~40% exit rate, nearly 2.5x the company average.

### Tech stack
Python · Pandas · Scikit-learn · Matplotlib · Seaborn · Jupyter Notebook

### Dataset
IBM HR Analytics Employee Attrition — via Kaggle
